               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Gadla Kiros “Vita of Kiros” (fols. 5ra-45rb)
 
                     Colophon.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">

                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>The Vita of Kiros is preceded by a short theological treatise on the
                        Trinity (<locus target="#5ra">5ra</locus>b).</note>
                     <colophon xml:id="coloph1">
                        <locus target="#45ra">45ra</locus>b: ተፈጸመ፡ ገድለ፡ ኪሮስ፡ በሰላመ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ አብ፡ አሜን፡
                        በ፲ወ፱፻፴ወ፮፡ ዓመተ፡ ምህረት፡ በዘበነ፡ ዮሐንስ፡ ወንጌላዊ፡ ሌሊቱ፡ ፪ መዓልቱ፡ ፳ወ፭፡ ዘጸሐፋኂ፡ አባ፡ ክንፈ፡
                        ገብርኤል፡ ፍስሐ።<locus target="#45ra">45ra</locus>b: The Vita of Kiros has been
                        completed in the peace of God the Father, amen. In the year of mercy 1936 in
                        the era of John the Evangelist, night 2, day 25. ʾAbbā Kǝnfa Gabrǝʾel Fǝssǝḥa
                        is the one who wrote it. The colophon states that the Ms. was completed in 1936
                        year of mercy (= 1943/44 A.D.) and that the scribe was ʾabbā Kǝnfa Gabrǝʾel
                        Fǝśśǝḥa. </colophon>
                  </msItem>
                  
               </msContents>
